Key Match Events: Jake Irvin gave up one run and two hits in six innings
CJ Abrams hit a 420-foot home run over the center-field wall
James Wood's on-base streak reached a career-high 12 games with two singles and an RBI
Post-Match Reflections: Braves manager Brian Snitker expressed frustration with the team's inability to score runs and support the pitching
Nationals manager Dave Martinez praised CJ Abrams' performance and his battle throughout the season
Miscellaneous Highlights: Atlanta Braves' Max Fried allowed four runs over six innings
Michael Harris II and Jorge Soler provided the Braves' first two hits of the game
Dylan Crews added a pair of hits for Washington, including a run-scoring single
The Nationals won 5-1, improving their record while the Braves fell one game behind the Mets in the NL wild card race
